<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--BoyTrapped     05-09 0154</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Boy Trapped,0158</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>13-Month-Old Boy Trapped In Cistern 2{ Hours</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELLINGHAM, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rescue workers dug a trench and broke
through concrete walls to save a 13-month-old boy who fell down a
foot-wide pipe into an unused water storage tank where he was
trapped for 2{ hours.
   Stephen Ulrich on Sunday was taken to St. Luke's Hospital where
he was released with just a couple scrapes, said nursing supervisor
Jo Sparks.
   ``I'd say he's a pretty lucky little boy,'' said police Sgt.
Greg Moore.
   Stephen apparently lifted a loose lid off the cistern when his
mother, Kim, went into the house briefly, Moore said. When she
heard screams, she ran outside and found the boy had fallen 6 feet
down the pipe and 4 feet into the storage area, which measured
about 6-by-8 feet, he said.
   The tank was about half filled with dirt, which helped break the
boy's fall, Moore said.
