<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The following is a text of a statement that
chief White House spokesman Marlin Fitzwater issued today in
response to the release of a new book by former White House chief
of staff Donald T. Regan:
   The new book by Donald Regan is a kiss-and-tell story in the
mold of all such books which seek to exploit the presidency or the
first family for personal self-interest.
   President Reagan expressed his view of these kinds of books
several days ago, indicating his deep personal disappointment in
this breach of confidence. In addition, the president emphasized
last week that he had made no policy decisions based on astrology.
   We also recognize that the first lady has an interest in
astrology. After the March 30 (1981) attempted assassination of the
president, she reached out to friends, to ministers, family and her
friend who advises on astrology. But we cannot comment on her
private communications with the chief of staff.
   Suffice to say we are very proud of the Reagan record, the
accomplishments of the administration in the last seven years and
the achievements and strengths of the president.
