<1ST_LINE>r a AM-People-Streisand     05-09 0218</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Streisand,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Has Heard Noises All Her Life</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: For release 6:30 p.m. EDT</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Barbra Streisand says she has been hearing
unusual noise since she was a child and it helped her understand
St. Joan, whose character she used for a radio audition when she
was 13.
   ``I knew she was telling the truth'' when she said she heard
voices, Streisand said in an interview in the June issue of Ladies
Home Journal.
   ``I don't hear voices, but I hear noise. All the time,'' the
singer said.
   Streisand evidently hears a wider range of sound on more levels
and registers than most people.
   ``Doctors can't do anything about it,'' she said. ``I used to
put scarves around my head to muffle the noises, but ... it only
made it worse. It's annoying and I've never gotten used to it.
Sometimes when I'm under more stress the noises become louder, but
if I'm having a good time I sort of forget it momentarily.''
   She also talked about her latest beau, Don Johnson, star of the
``Miami Vice'' television series.
   ``When I'm with Don, I can enjoy my celebrity because I don't
have to apologize to the man I'm with for getting all the
attention,'' she said. ``Don gets as much attention as I do.''
</TEXT>
