<HEAD>Dream of Owning Tropical Island? It Could Be Yours</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   If you dream of owning your own island in the
sun, this could be your summer.
   Those folks at MTV _ who in the past have given away a house and
a town _ teamed up with Coca-Cola for a summer sweepstakes
promotion with an uninhabited Caribbean island as top prize.
   ``They say it's lovely,'' said rock singer Cyndi Lauper, on hand
Monday at a Manhattan restaurant to promote the contest. ``It does
have water on all four sides. Which makes it an island.''
   The promoters would say nothing specific about the landscape or
cost of the 25-acre island two miles off Ponce, Puerto Rico.
   But, said Harriet Seitler, an MTV marketing executive, ``It
would probably require a great deal of initiative'' to make it
liveable.
   The island will be awarded by Miss Lauper to one of 225
sweepstakes winners of a Caribbean cruise in July.
   The performer, who'll be making her first trip on a cruise ship,
said, ``Maybe I'll do a little singing. Maybe you'll do a little
singing. But I do watch `Love Boat' so I know what goes on during
these cruises.''
   Miss Lauper, who's joining the contest to help push a new record
and her movie ``Vibes'' with Jeff Goldblum and Peter Falk, promises
the winners plenty of chances to see the film.
   ``The good thing about this cruise is it could be my movie every
night. I think I'd like that,'' she said.
