<HEAD>Soldier Wounded In Attack At TV Transmitter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unidentified men in a van fired at
troops guarding a television transmitter late today, wounding at
least one soldier, the military said.
   Sgt. Estelito Cadag of the Philippine Constabulary's Capital
Command said the shooting continued for more than 30 minutes as the
troops, in their confusion, also fired at responding policemen and
soldiers.
   ``The guards thought that the responding troops belonged to the
same group that had attacked them,'' Cadag said by telephone.
   He said an investigation was under way to determine the
identities of the men in the van and establish the reason for the
attack. Cadag said the attack occurred at 10 p.m.
   Dozens of troops rushed to the Kanlaon Broadcasting System
transmitter in suburban Quezon City and other broadcast facilities
in the capital to increase security at the installations.
   Military guards were posted at various radio and television
stations in the capital following at least six coup attempts
against President Corazon Aquino's government during the past two
years.
</TEXT>
