<HEAD>Selleck Says He's Happy with `Magnum, P.I.' Finale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONOLULU (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Tom Selleck _ now officially unemployed _
says he watched the two-hour ``Magnum, P.I.'' finale at co-star
Larry Manetti's house in Los Angeles, and is thrilled the show
clobbered its competition.
   The final episode of the CBS series, which aired May 1, topped
the week's ratings.
   ``I'm delighted the show went out such a winner,'' Selleck said.
