could happen to the show,'' Selleck said in the The Sunday
Star-Bulletin and Advertiser.
   Selleck said he starts work on a new movie in July, and will
take it easy until then.
   ``I'm going to disappear,'' he said. ``I am officially
unemployed.''
   The last time he was out of work was in 1980, but then he wasn't
so grateful for the free time. He arrived in Honolulu expecting to
begin filming ``Magnum.'' But the Screen Actors Guild went on
strike, and Selleck had no regular paycheck.
   ``I went to work for $7 an hour for my landlady as a handyman to
help pay the rent,'' he said.
