<1ST_LINE>r w AM-Reagan-SmallBusiness     05-09 0308</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Reagan-Small Business,300</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reagan Says Climate Has Never Been Better For Entrepreneurs</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan said Monday that each year of
his administration has seen ``unparalleled growth'' of small
business and that the climate has never been better for
entrepeneurs.
   ``The record, quite simply, is incredible,'' he said at a Rose
Garden ceremony honoring small business. ``Small business provides
well over two-thirds of all new jobs; about 40 percent of our
aggregate national output; the bulk of new products and
technologies; most of the jobs generated for younger, older and
female workers; and over 66 percent of all `first jobs.'''
   Reagan said the past five years have seen the longest unbroken
period of peacetime growth on record.
   ``The climate necessary to nurture small business development
has never been better,'' Reagan said. ``Clearly the econopmic
policies of the 1980s ... have made it immensely easier to start up
a small business and keep it going.''
   The ceremony coincided with the administration's seventh report
to Congress on the state of small business.
   ``Small business news continues to be good news,'' the report
said. ``The continuation of this strong small business record is a
national priority.''
   Reagan presented plaques as ``Business Persons of the year'' to
boyhood friends Ben Cohen and Jerry Greenfield, who started Ben and
Jerry's Homemade Inc. of South Burlington, Vt., and made it the
third largest distributor in U.S.
   ``Beginning with two employees in 1978, the company now employs
200, and the $8,000 in start-up money now generates annual sales of
$30 million selling to grocery stores in 35 states and in 45 ice
cream parlors around the country,'' Reagan said.
   The president also told the White House guests that ``small
business is about hopes and dreams,'' making dreams come true.
``Those dreams, those hopes,'' he said, ``are a singular and great
natural resource.''
</TEXT>
