   Here is a list of some of the women who became important world
leaders:
   
   Golda Meir, prime minister of Israel, 1969-74.
   Indira Gandhi, prime minister of India, 1966-77 and 1980-84.
   Gro Harlem Brundtland, prime minister of Norway, 1981 and
1986-present.
   Corazon Aquino, president of The Philippines, 1986-present.
   Isabel Peron, president of Argentina, 1974-76.
   Vigdis Finnbogadottir, president of Iceland, 1980-present.
   Margaret Thatcher, prime minister of Great Britain, 1979-present.
   Mary Eugenia Charles, prime minister of Dominica, 1980-present.
   Sirimavo Bandaranaike, prime minister of Sri Lanka, 1960-65 and
1970-77.
   
   Reigning female monarchs:
   
   Elizabeth II of England, 1952-present.
   Margrethe II of Denmark, 1972-present.
   Beatrix of The Netherlands, 1980-present:
   
   Ceremonial heads of state:
   
   Agtha Barbara, president of Malta, 1982-present.
   Jeanne Suave, governor-general of Canada, 1985-present.
