<1ST_LINE>u f PM-MohascoBuyout     05-09 0222</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Mohasco Buyout,0230</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>MHS Holdings Agrees on Mohasco Takeover</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FAIRFAX, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mohasco Corp., a manufacturer and
distributor of commercial and residential furnishings, has agreed
to be taken over by MHS Holdings Corp. in a deal worth more than
$456 million, the companies said today.
   MHS, a newly organized group of investors, will submit a tender
offer by May 13 of $36.50 for each of 12.5 million shares of
Mohasco common stock, which is just over 93 percent of the
company's outstanding shares.
   The tender offer is to be followed by a merger in which each of
the remaining shares of stock will be exchanged for a new issue of
notes, which will be worth $36.50, in the opinion of the financial
advisers to both parties.
   The offer is subject to the approval of two-thirds of the
outstanding Mohasco shares and the obtaining of financing for the
transaction.
   Wall Street reacted to the announcement by sending Mohasco's
stock up $1.50 per share, to $35.62{ per share, on the New York
Stock Exchange by midday.
   Mohasco manufactures, distributes and rents commercial and
residential interior furnishings. Among its hldings are Mohawk
Carpets, the Barcalounger and Stratolounger lines of reclining
chairs and the Cort Furniture Rental company of Washington, D.C.
   HMS Holdings includes Citicorp Capital Investors Ltd. and the
Mutual Series Fund Inc.
</TEXT>
