<HEAD>Kleinwort Confirms Talks With Fuji On U.S. Primary Dealership</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kleinwort Benson Ltd. said it has been negotiating
with Fuji Bank Ltd. over the past several months to sell a large
portion of Kleinwort Benson Government Securities Inc., its
Chicago-based primary dealership.
   The proposal to sell a 24.9 percent stake has been discussed
with regulators in the United States, Japan and Britain, but a
formal application has not yet been filed, Kleinwort said in a
statement.
   Kleinwort refused to comment further, except to say a further
statement would be made ``in due course.''
   A U.S. primary dealership is a government securities firm to
which the Federal Reserve trades directly in an attempt to control
monetary policy.
   Published reports in Tokyo have said the Fed is showing
opposition to Fuji's purchase or capital participation in
Kleinworth's government securities unit.
