<1ST_LINE>r f AM-RJRAdvertising     05-09 0241</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-RJR Advertising,0251</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>RJR Nabisco Shifts Advertising Assignments</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   RJR Nabisco Inc. announced Monday a consolidation
of its advertising business, shifting some major assignments from
three agencies to others who already handle much of the tobacco and
food giant's accounts.
   RJR Nabisco said it had awarded contracts for several Nabisco
cookie products to FCB-Leber Katz Partners, a division of
Chicago-based Foote, Cone & Belding Communications Inc. FCB-Leber
Katz also will split responsibility for advertising for Planters
LifeSavers products with other agencies.
   Both those accounts, estimated at about $80 million, had been
handled by Saatchi & Saatchi DFS Inc. RJR fired Saatchi recently
after the agency created a no-smoking campaign for Northwest
Airlines.
   In addition to its food business, RJR is a major cigarette maker.
   FCB-Leber Katz already handles Salem and Vantage cigarettes,
Nabisco cereals, pet snacks and Royal desserts for RJR.
   Other agencies losing business in the consolidation were
Tatham-Laird & Kudner of Chicago and Bozell, Jacobs, Kenyon &
Eckhardt, based in New York.
   FCB-Leber Katz was awarded the assignment of making ads for
Fleischmann's margarine and Egg Beaters, formerly assigned to
Tatham-Laird.
   The ad agency Lowe Marschalk, one of the Interpublic Group of
Companies' agencies which already has some RJR food assignments,
got Ortega Mexican foods, formerly handled by Tatham-Laird.
   Another Interpublic agency, Lintas USA, was assigned Planters
nuts and snacks, and Baby Ruth and Butterfinger candy bars. Those
assignments had formerly been handled by Bozell, Jacobs.
</TEXT>
