<1ST_LINE>d f AM-AutoIncentives     05-09 0302</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Incentives,0314</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chrysler Announces Incentives on Wide Range of Models</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JANET BRAUNSTEIN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Auto Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Corp. announced a buyer incentive
campaign on Monday, offering rebates of up to $1,500 on several
models and cut-rate financing.
   Chrysler has used aggressive incentive campaigns and pricing
strategies throughout the year in an attempt to increase its sales.
   The incentives announced Monday include $400 rebates on the 1987
and 1988 Plymouth Reliant and Dodge Aries, the K-cars which already
are being marketed as low-priced America series models.
   Instead of rebates, buyers may choose financing ranging from 5.8
percent annually on 48-month loans and 9.8 percent on 60-month
loans. On Eagle Premier, Chrysler offered 8.8 percent financing for
up to 72 months.
   Chrysler is offering a $500 rebate on 1987 and 1988 Plymouth
Sundance-Dodge Shadow subcompacts, imported Dodge and Plymouth Colt
subcompacts and the sporty Dodge Daytona.
   Trucks covered by the $500 rebate include the 1987 and 1988
imported two-wheel-drive Ram 50 compact pickup, imported Dodge
Raider sport-utility vehicle, Dodge Dakota mid-size pickup,
standard Ram B150, 250 and 350 vans and wagons, Jeep Wagoneer,
two-door Jeep Cherokee, and two-wheel-drive short-bed Jeep Comanche
pickup.
   Chrysler is offering a $750 rebate on the 1988 Eagle Premier
sedan and on 1987 and 1988 cars including Dodge Lancer-Chrysler
LeBaron GTS and the imported Dodge and Plymouth Colt Vista.
   On trucks, buyers can get a $750 rebate on 1987 and 1988
four-wheel-drive Ram 50, two-wheel-drive long-bed Jeep Comanche and
the four-wheel-drive Comanche.
   Rebates of $1,000 are available on 1988 Eagle Medallion compact
and 1987 and 1988 Chrysler LeBaron coupe, except for convertible
models, 1988 Dodge Daytona Shelby Z, Jeep Grand Wagoneer and
standard Ram 100, 150, 250 and 350 pickups.
   Chrysler is offering $1,500 rebates on 1987 and 1988 Dodge
Daytona Pacifica and Chrysler Conquest.
</TEXT>
